<h1>Fischer Indole Synthesis</h1>
<p><img src="Fische1.gif" width="318" height="92"></p>
<p>The 
conversion of aryl hydrazones to indoles; requires elevated temperatures 
and the addition of Brønsted or Lewis acids. Some interesting 
enhancements have been published recently; for example a milder 
conversion when
<i>N</i>-trifluoroacetyl enehydrazines are used as substrates. (<a href="../abstracts/literature/529.shtm">abstract</a>).</p>
<hr>
<h2>Mechanism of the Fischer Indole Synthesis</h2>
<p><img src="Fische3.gif" width="554" height="235">&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<div style="margin: 15 0 5 -7; padding: 7 4 7 4; border: 1px solid #DDDDDD; clear:both">
